text: Al Shabhana () is a village in western Qatar located in the municipality of Al-Shahaniya. It is located about east of Umm Bab and about southwest of Al Kharsaah. The city of Dukhan is approximately northwest of Al Shabhana. ==Etymology== A plant known locally as shabhan, found in abundance in a nearby rawda (depression), gave the village its name. ==Sport== In the 2013 Qatar International Rally, Al Shabhana was included as a stage for the first time, and runs for . ==References== Category:Populated places in Al-Shahaniya
title: Al Shabhana
